                            <comment id="13991802" author="dkulp" created="Wed, 7 May 2014 13:23:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why should this not be faultcode:Client?   According to the soap spec:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;The Client &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;of errors indicate that the message was incorrectly formed or did not contain the appropriate information in order to succeed
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which is exactly what a schema validation error is.  It&apos;s a message that is incorrectly formed.    Thus, in this case, the fault code SHOULD be Client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
